but small fry.

130
00:06:32,550 --> 00:06:34,110
Not even enough to cover the gas money.

131
00:06:39,670 --> 00:06:40,200
Thanks.

132
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,550
Lv Yuan didn't take her vacuum with her?

133
00:06:48,155 --> 00:06:50,110
She and her daughter were crying
their eyes out

134
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:51,430
when they left.

135
00:06:51,755 --> 00:06:52,911
Didn't have time to grab it.

136
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:54,080
I'll drop it off later.

137
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:55,960
They cried?

138
00:06:58,230 --> 00:07:00,870
Now I understand
what Lv Xinghuo went through.

139
00:07:01,350 --> 00:07:03,480
She's had it rough all these years.

140
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,520
Ms. Lv's great in every way, right?

141
00:07:05,590 --> 00:07:06,040
Yes.

142
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,790
But she's really controlling.

143
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:11,120
She drove her ex-husband crazy
with all the nagging.

144
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:13,950
That's why he cheated,
and the divorce got so messy.

145
00:07:15,550 --> 00:07:16,480
Really?

146
00:07:16,710 --> 00:07:17,640
Why would I lie?

147
00:07:18,590 --> 00:07:20,640
Even Ms. Lv admitted it in the end.

148
00:07:21,333 --> 00:07:23,577
The more you try to control someone,
the more they run.

149
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,400
You've got to learn to let go.

150
00:07:26,670 --> 00:07:27,240
So true.

151
00:07:27,266 --> 00:07:28,550
Can't control people too much.

152
00:07:29,622 --> 00:07:30,790
What's that supposed to mean?

153
00:07:32,670 --> 00:07:33,160
Nothing.

154
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,400
Dad's right.

155
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,910
Where there's oppression,
there's resistance.

156
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,710
You can't have people
controlling people.

157
00:07:42,790 --> 00:07:43,240
No control?

158
00:07:43,577 --> 00:07:45,380
If I let you loose,
you'll be off the rails!

159
00:07:45,910 --> 00:07:47,280
There you go again, Mom.

160
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:48,590
Listen.

161
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,280
Even I've seen enough.

162
00:07:50,622 --> 00:07:51,910
Dad doesn't have many hobbies.

163
00:07:51,910 --> 00:07:53,040
He likes fishing.

164
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,520
And he does it at wild ponds.

165
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:55,190
It's free.

166
00:07:56,190 --> 00:07:58,360
He needs a bit of social life
with his fishing buddies.

167
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,280
You could at least
give him a bit of cash.

168
00:08:00,311 --> 00:08:01,710
Otherwise, people will laugh at him.

169
00:08:05,590 --> 00:08:06,640
Like she would agree.

170
00:08:09,622 --> 00:08:11,466
You make me sound like
I'm some stingy miser.

171
00:08:14,190 --> 00:08:15,400
Fine. You want money?

172
00:08:15,670 --> 00:08:16,488
I'll send it to you.

173
00:08:16,911 --> 00:08:17,550
I'll do it.

174
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:20,422
I'll send it right now.

175
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:21,590
You...

176
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:22,670
1,000 yuan.

177
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:23,400
There!

178
00:08:23,910 --> 00:08:25,070
Spend it however you like!

179
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,830
What can you even do
with 1,000 yuan, huh Dad?

180
00:08:28,355 --> 00:08:29,400
She actually sent it!

181
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,880
She's being generous today.

182
00:08:33,070 --> 00:08:33,880
Usually getting her

183
00:08:34,040 --> 00:08:35,670
