If something comes to mind,

564
00:26:18,310 --> 00:26:19,550
do it.

565
00:26:21,070 --> 00:26:22,040
If you miss the chance,

566
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:23,790
you might miss it forever.

567
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:26,800
That's why the moment
I saw that video of Le Shuishan,

568
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:28,200
I couldn't wait a second longer.

569
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:30,480
I just wanted to come back.
I just wanted to see her.

570
00:26:31,550 --> 00:26:32,110
Qing...

571
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:38,790
I miss Mom...

572
00:26:45,709 --> 00:26:49,020
(Chaihuo Wontons)

573
00:26:54,110 --> 00:26:55,110
Where's my thanks, hm?

574
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:57,040
I carried this all the way back for you.

575
00:26:57,760 --> 00:26:59,040
I really appreciate it, Aunt.

576
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:01,040
This thing is heavy!

577
00:27:01,555 --> 00:27:02,790
"Welcome home" tangyuan for you.

578
00:27:02,955 --> 00:27:04,150
I'll make you a feast tomorrow.

579
00:27:04,350 --> 00:27:05,040
Thanks, Lina.

580
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:08,350
Slow down. Don't burn yourself.

581
00:27:09,590 --> 00:27:10,150
All right.

582
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:11,070
Tell us.

583
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:13,590
Why did you suddenly come back?

584
00:27:13,822 --> 00:27:15,022
Is something the matter?

585
00:27:16,777 --> 00:27:18,088
Of course something's up, Dad.

586
00:27:18,155 --> 00:27:19,755
Is missing home a big enough reason?

587
00:27:21,488 --> 00:27:22,320
- Qing?
- Of course.

588
00:27:22,355 --> 00:27:23,844
Is missing Mom a big enough reason?

589
00:27:28,830 --> 00:27:29,110
Dad.

590
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:31,720
I took my brother
to see Le Shuishan today.

591
00:27:31,933 --> 00:27:33,310
Her qipao team had a performance.

592
00:27:34,390 --> 00:27:34,760
You...

593
00:27:36,870 --> 00:27:37,440
You two...

594
00:27:38,377 --> 00:27:39,310
You're something else.

595
00:27:39,790 --> 00:27:41,200
There was a moment

596
00:27:41,630 --> 00:27:43,280
when I truly felt like she was Mom.

597
00:27:44,310 --> 00:27:46,480
I've always felt like
I owed her one last family meal.

598
00:27:47,070 --> 00:27:48,480
She left with regrets.

599
00:27:50,310 --> 00:27:51,630
And I'm living with mine.

600
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:53,760
So, my dear father,

601
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:55,110
can we please

602
00:27:55,133 --> 00:27:57,555
invite Ms. Le over for dinner
this Mid-Autumn Festival?

603
00:27:58,333 --> 00:27:59,790
I don't think that's appropriate.

604
00:28:01,150 --> 00:28:02,520
Why wouldn't it be?

605
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,110
I just want her to sit there,

606
00:28:05,177 --> 00:28:06,760
and for all of us to gather around her.

607
00:28:06,822 --> 00:28:08,688
She doesn't need to do anything
but look at us.

608
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:10,110
But she's not Mom.

609
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:11,520
Doesn't matter if she is or isn't.

610
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:12,870
When I look at that face, she is.

611
00:28:13,590 --> 00:28:13,960
Dad,

612
00:28:14,550 --> 00:28:16,760
just this once, please let me have this?

613
00:28:17,110 --> 00:28:19,590
I just want to use
Mom's favorite purple clay teacup

614
00:28:19,590 --> 00:28:20,040
and

615
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:21,630
pour her favorite tea.

616
00:28:21,870 --> 00:28:23,550
I'd just like her to sit there, smile,

617
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:25,040
and look at us.

618
00:28:31,150 --> 00:28:32,110
To tell you the truth,

619
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:34,310
there are times

620
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:36,760
when I glance at her,

621
00:28:39,070 --> 00:28:41,720
and think she really is your mom.

622
00:28:41,870 --> 00:28:42,440
Right?

623
00:28:44,040 --> 00:28:46,110
Then invite her.

624
00:28:50,110 --> 00:28:51,040
I'll give it a shot.

625
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:54,870
You're the head of the house.
It's your call.

626
00:28:57,222 --> 00:28:57,830
Give it a shot.

627
00:28:58,520 --> 00:28:58,830
Okay.

628
00:29:11,150 --> 00:29:11,920
How do you feel?

629
00:29:13,110 --> 00:29:15,150
All that sweating really helps
relieve stress.

630
00:29:15,350 --> 00:29:16,000
Right?

631
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:19,310
"Nature is an excellent sedative."

632
00:29:19,688 --> 00:29:21,000
That's what Chekhov said.

633
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:25,830
Recently, we met someone

634
00:29:26,150 --> 00:29:27,630
who looks just like my mom.

635
00:29:28,390 --> 00:29:29,790
Our whole family was shocked.

636
00:29:30,488 --> 00:29:31,844
How much does she look like her?

637
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:34,960
Facial recognition software
said 92% similarity

638
00:29:35,390 --> 00:29:36,680
with no blood relation.

639
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,040
Wow, that's serious.

640
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:41,070
My sister

641
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:44,200
even flew back from overseas
just because of this.

642
00:29:44,300 --> 00:29:47,111
And now she's insisting we invite
the woman to our house for dinner.

643
00:29:47,350 --> 00:29:48,480
Feels a bit abrupt to me.

644
00:29:50,790 --> 00:29:52,680
Well, meeting someone is fate.

645
00:29:52,955 --> 00:29:55,039
Their being alike
makes it even more special.

646
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:55,888
You should meet her.

647
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:09,390
♪In the garden late at night,
all is hushed and still...♪

648
00:30:09,390 --> 00:30:10,720
It came out great.

649
00:30:11,150 --> 00:30:11,760
Not bad at all.

650
00:30:11,822 --> 00:30:12,288
Excellent.

651
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:12,760
Good.

652
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:15,200
The Wind and Rainbow Choir

653
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:16,200
is well-known now.

654
00:30:16,350 --> 00:30:17,760
We might want to consider expanding.

655
00:30:18,790 --> 00:30:21,350
We should bring
Ms. Le Shuishan on board.

656
00:30:24,040 --> 00:30:24,760
You know what?

657
00:30:25,790 --> 00:30:26,310
Gou,

658
00:30:27,630 --> 00:30:29,200
I think

659
00:30:29,888 --> 00:30:30,790
that's a great idea.

660
00:30:31,350 --> 00:30:32,110
I'm all for it.

661
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:33,150
Me too.

662
00:30:33,790 --> 00:30:35,200
"Unbidden...

663
00:30:35,310 --> 00:30:36,350
the memories come."

664
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:41,240
You've still got your wits, Ding.

665
00:30:54,790 --> 00:30:55,955
I'll come pick you up later.

666
00:31:02,870 --> 00:31:03,280
Bye.

667
00:31:07,733 --> 00:31:10,160
(Welcome, Le Shuishan!)
This song has been around for a while.

668
00:31:10,280 --> 00:31:11,070
She's here!

669
00:31:12,310 --> 00:31:13,070
She's here!

670
00:31:14,870 --> 00:31:15,550
Ms. Le.

671
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:16,310
Come in.

672
00:31:16,630 --> 00:31:17,150
Welcome!

673
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:19,630
Come in.

674
00:31:23,150 --> 00:31:24,480
Welcome, Ms. Le!

675
00:31:25,350 --> 00:31:26,200
It's an honor

676
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:27,830
to have you with us.

677
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:30,350
Now that Ms. Le's here,

678
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:32,440
the visuals of our choir

679
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:33,870
just leveled up!

680
00:31:35,390 --> 00:31:37,070
Zhou, better watch out.

681
00:31:37,630 --> 00:31:39,520
Your wife keeps a tight leash.

682
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:44,040
Welcome!

683
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:47,280
I'm Le Shuishan,

684
00:31:47,790 --> 00:31:48,480
the new member.

685
00:31:48,870 --> 00:31:49,920
Please take care of me.

686
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:52,870
You're Mr. Shen?

687
00:31:53,760 --> 00:31:54,040
Yes.

688
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:56,520
Mr. Shen Zhuoran?

689
00:31:56,777 --> 00:31:57,240
That's me.

690
00:31:58,550 --> 00:32:00,110
No wonder I thought you looked familiar

691
00:32:00,110 --> 00:32:01,920
when I did your makeup the other day.

692
00:32:03,150 --> 00:32:06,240
You were on the provincial channel's
reading program once.

693
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:07,070
Yes.

694
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:10,390
The Literary Beauty of Kun Opera.

695
00:32:11,111 --> 00:32:11,790
That's right.

696
00:32:11,866 --> 00:32:12,630
That's the event.

697
00:32:13,630 --> 00:32:14,000
Yes.

698
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,110
I was there.

699
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:16,960
You said,

700
00:32:18,070 --> 00:32:20,390
"In life,
there are no better or worse paths.

701
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:22,240
Just different ones."

702
00:32:23,280 --> 00:32:24,350
That really stuck with me.

703
00:32:25,350 --> 00:32:26,350
Talk about fate.

704
00:32:28,150 --> 00:32:28,680
Ms. Le.

705
00:32:29,550 --> 00:32:30,630
This must be fate.

706
00:32:32,150 --> 00:32:34,040
Fate is up to the heavens.

707
00:32:34,110 --> 00:32:35,590
Action is up to us.

708
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:37,150
What

709
00:32:37,440 --> 00:32:38,360
do you mean?

710
00:32:39,190 --> 00:32:41,040
Before Gou even called me,

711
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:44,520
I had already asked Dean Xu to help

712
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:47,590
recommend me to the choir.

713
00:32:48,230 --> 00:32:50,630
Then, when Gou called to invite me,

714
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:52,710
I was over the moon!

715
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:57,440
Me and the Wind and Rainbow Choir
were meant to find each other.

716
00:32:58,670 --> 00:33:00,000
Indeed!

717
00:33:00,977 --> 00:33:01,800
Beautifully said!

718
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:02,590
Wonderful!

719
00:33:03,230 --> 00:33:03,840
Mr. Shen.

720
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:07,230
Could I get your autograph?

721
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:10,840
You even brought the book?

722
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:12,670
How thoughtful.

723
00:33:13,155 --> 00:33:14,110
I'll sign it right now.

724
00:33:19,230 --> 00:33:20,440
Where should I sign?

725
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:21,880
Here, or...

726
00:33:22,590 --> 00:33:24,040
Just right here. The first page.

727
00:33:24,190 --> 00:33:24,880
All right.

728
00:33:25,688 --> 00:33:26,190
Will that do?

729
00:33:28,666 --> 00:33:31,260
(The Literary Beauty of Kun Opera
by Le Shuishan)

730
00:33:32,270 --> 00:33:35,040
Haven't seen a man
use a fountain pen in a long time.

731
00:33:38,270 --> 00:33:39,150
How sophisticated.

732
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:42,190
Ding.

733
00:33:43,040 --> 00:33:43,960
Come here, Ding.

734
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:51,150
Your handwriting is beautiful.

735
00:33:56,750 --> 00:33:57,750
Thank you.

736
00:34:02,480 --> 00:34:02,920
Dad.

737
00:34:04,150 --> 00:34:05,920
Le Shuishan joined your choir?

738
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:06,520
Yes.

739
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:08,520
Did you invite her to dinner

740
00:34:08,520 --> 00:34:09,480
for Mid-Autumn yet?

741
00:34:09,670 --> 00:34:10,960
Not yet.

742
00:34:11,190 --> 00:34:12,630
Today was just our first rehearsal.

743
00:34:13,040 --> 00:34:14,230
Inviting her now

744
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:16,040
would feel too abrupt.

745
00:34:17,444 --> 00:34:17,960
That's true.

746
00:34:18,750 --> 00:34:20,070
We'll have plenty of chances.

747
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,110
That's true.

748
00:34:21,750 --> 00:34:22,110
Oh,

749
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:23,800
and she even

750
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:26,230
brought one of my books today

751
00:34:26,670 --> 00:34:27,840
and asked for an autograph.

752
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:29,400
Really?

753
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,800
Le Shuishan's a fan of yours, Dad?

754
00:34:32,590 --> 00:34:34,150
- Of course.
- You never know.

755
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:36,070
Dad's got charm.

756
00:34:36,555 --> 00:34:37,190
Oh right, Dad.

757
00:34:37,750 --> 00:34:40,040
Try on this new shirt I brought you!

758
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:43,670
You've got to look your best
at choir practice from now on.

759
00:34:45,866 --> 00:34:46,800
I don't like the color.

760
00:34:47,880 --> 00:34:49,710
It's bright. It suits you.

761
00:34:49,710 --> 00:34:51,400
Look at what Mr. Gou wears.

762
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:52,800
I can't compare to him.

763
00:34:52,900 --> 00:34:54,520
And this thing
doesn't even have pockets.

764
00:34:54,622 --> 00:34:56,533
Where am I supposed
to put my fountain pen?

765
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:57,840
Who still carries pens

766
00:34:57,840 --> 00:34:59,000
in their shirts these days?

767
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:02,880
I do.

768
00:35:08,630 --> 00:35:09,880
Maybe she likes that about him.

769
00:35:14,466 --> 00:35:15,466
Here, you take it.

770
00:35:16,270 --> 00:35:16,630
Dad.

771
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:19,110
I'll get you one with pockets
for your fountain pen.

772
00:35:25,190 --> 00:35:27,000
Oh, good. You're here. Try this one on.

773
00:35:27,088 --> 00:35:28,040
Your sister bought it.

774
00:35:28,520 --> 00:35:29,270
I'll try it later.

775
00:35:29,270 --> 00:35:31,150
I'm heading to Xuanwu Lake for a run.

776
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:33,840
It's not like you're catching a flight.

777
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:35,550
What's the rush?

778
00:35:36,070 --> 00:35:37,320
And Xuanwu Lake?

779
00:35:37,550 --> 00:35:38,920
Takes an hour round-trip

780
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,270
and parking is expensive.

781
00:35:40,270 --> 00:35:41,555
Can't you just run near home?

782
00:35:42,288 --> 00:35:43,960
You weren't happy when I had back pain.

783
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:45,950
And you still aren't happy
now that I'm running.

784
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:47,800
The running group at Xuanwu Lake

785
00:35:48,270 --> 00:35:49,150
has great vibes.

786
00:35:49,630 --> 00:35:50,110
Fine.

787
00:35:50,520 --> 00:35:52,230
But try this on first.

788
00:35:52,666 --> 00:35:54,190
You're looking sprightly these days.

789
00:35:54,190 --> 00:35:55,590
This color fits you perfectly.

790
00:35:55,622 --> 00:35:57,511
You'll be the most stylish one
in the group.

791
00:35:59,230 --> 00:36:01,040
Are you sure this suits me?

792
00:36:01,710 --> 00:36:02,590
No thanks.

793
00:36:03,590 --> 00:36:04,040
Take it.

794
00:36:04,040 --> 00:36:06,110
So hard to please.
Okay, not giving it to you then.

795
00:36:07,070 --> 00:36:07,480
I'm off.

796
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,070
Most dedicated runner ever.

797
00:36:11,800 --> 00:36:14,110
Let's eat. Try the fish head.

798
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:19,070
Eat more, little boy. Eat up.

799
00:36:19,750 --> 00:36:20,920
Gentlemen. Everyone.

800
00:36:21,550 --> 00:36:22,710
How are you finding the food?

801
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:24,000
This clay pot fish head

802
00:36:24,177 --> 00:36:25,040
is pretty authentic.

803
00:36:25,355 --> 00:36:27,040
Now this is someone who knows food.

804
00:36:27,190 --> 00:36:27,920
Good taste.

805
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:28,920
What's your last name?

806
00:36:29,070 --> 00:36:29,480
Liu.

807
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:31,320
Liu, allow me to give you a toast.

808
00:36:31,630 --> 00:36:32,270
Let me tell you.

809
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:33,550
This clay pot fish head

810
00:36:33,550 --> 00:36:35,150
is a local specialty.

811
00:36:35,590 --> 00:36:37,070
I made it myself.

812
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:40,360
Liu.

813
00:36:41,110 --> 00:36:43,190
You brought us to a great place.

814
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:46,630
My son-in-law recommended it.

815
00:36:47,070 --> 00:36:48,800
If he says it's good, it must be good.

816
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:50,880
Another toast to Liu!

817
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:52,150
To Liu!

818
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:53,360
Cheers!

819
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:54,230
Thank you.

820
00:36:54,550 --> 00:36:55,630
You're welcome.

821
00:36:56,070 --> 00:36:56,880
Let me tell you.

822
00:36:57,440 --> 00:37:01,000
I admire men who fish.

823
00:37:01,550 --> 00:37:02,150
Why's that?

824
00:37:03,150 --> 00:37:03,800
First,

825
00:37:04,710 --> 00:37:05,630
they're patient.

826
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:07,400
Right.

827
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:08,920
Second,

828
00:37:09,550 --> 00:37:10,880
it takes real skill.

829
00:37:11,230 --> 00:37:11,710
Definitely.

830
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:14,320
And third,

831
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:18,880
those old fishing guys,
out there in wind and rain.

832
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:20,440
That's the real deal.

833
00:37:23,230 --> 00:37:23,670
Ma'am!

834
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:24,880
The bill is on me!

835
00:37:25,066 --> 00:37:26,190
Nobody fights me on this!

836
00:37:28,190 --> 00:37:28,920
I'm paying!

837
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:29,800
Don't fight!

838
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:31,630
I'm paying!

839
00:37:31,630 --> 00:37:32,810
Don't bother fighting over it.

840
00:37:32,810 --> 00:37:34,330
The bill's already been taken care of.

841
00:37:35,466 --> 00:37:36,710
- Guess who paid?
- Who paid?

842
00:37:36,710 --> 00:37:37,230
Was it you?

843
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:37,960
Guess!

844
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:38,480
Who paid?

845
00:37:39,070 --> 00:37:39,550
Come on now.

846
00:37:39,550 --> 00:37:40,000
Who paid?

847
00:37:40,110 --> 00:37:41,070
Let's all

848
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:43,800
